{{Quote|Where's your sense of chivalry, Han?''"<br />"''Near as I can recall, I traded it for a ten-carat chrysopaz and three bottles of good brandy about five years ago on Commenor.|Luke Skywalker and Han Solo|<ref name="IVn">[[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope'' novelization]]</ref>}}
'''Chrysopaz''' was a translucent, yellowish gem.<ref name="GSWU" /> The [[Ryn/Legends|Ryn]] settlers of an [[unidentified planetoid]] in the [[Corporate Sector/Legends|Corporate Sector]] once offered to pay [[Dexter Jettster/Legends|Dexter Jettster]] a small fortune in chrysopaz and [[Aurodium/Legends|aurodium]] after he brought them equipment with which they could defend themselves against a group of overzealous tax collectors and their [[Security Police/Legends|Security Police]] enforcers. Jettster refused, however, instead settling for an ancient Ryn technique of making [[Ardees/Legends|Jawa juice]] in payment.<ref name="DD">{{Hyperspace|url=fans/hyperspace/source/dexdiner/index.html|text=Dining at Dex's|int=Dining at Dex's}}</ref> [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] once commented that he traded his sense of chivalry for a ten-carat chrysopaz and three bottles of [[Brandy/Legends|brandy]] on [[Commenor/Legends|Commenor]] when [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] was trying to convince him to [[Rescue of Princess Leia/Legends|rescue]] [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] from the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]].<ref name="IVn" /> During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], chrysopaz was valued anywhere from 5 to 2,000 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] per [[Coruscant Standard Carat]].<ref name="PP" /> In [[11 ABY/Legends|11 ABY]], [[Duchess]] [[Mistal]] offered a large reward of chrysopaz and [[firefacet]] gems for the return of her consort, [[Dack]]. After [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] resolved the situation, he was paid the full reward which equaled over a million credits.<ref name="JS">''[[Jedi Search]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Chrysopaz is misspelled "chrystopaz" in the gemstones table on page 38 of ''[[Pirates & Privateers]]'', and "chyrstopaz" on page 164 of the supplement ''[[The Far Orbit Project]]''.

